liberate /ˈlɪbəˌreɪt/

(liberating,liberated,liberates) 

1. V-T To liberate a place or the people in it means to free them from the political or military control of another country, area, or group of people. 解放 

例： They planned to march on and liberate the city. 他们打算继续前进解放这座城市。 

2. liberation N-UNCOUNT 解放 

例： ...a mass liberation movement. …一场大众解放运动。 

3. V-T To liberate someone from something means to help them escape from it or overcome it, and lead a better way of life. 使解脱 

例： He asked how committed the leadership was to liberating its people from poverty. 他问领导层让人民脱贫的态度有多么坚决。 

4. liberating ADJ 解脱的 

例： If you have the chance to spill your problems out to a therapist it can be a very liberating experience. 如果有机会向治疗专家倾诉问题，那会是一种让人非常解脱的体验。

